title: Samsung Polycarbonate Galaxy Z Fold6 S-Pen Case,Navy
top_review: Update* :----------After just 2 weeks of usage the back part has started turning yellow at the touch points i.e. entire corner just below which covers the volume rocker and power button & right corner of s-pen holder. When viewed from back face, its not immediately noticeable, but from side view its significantly visible.Strangely, the front part hasn't developed any yellowing effect as of yet, which makes me believe that both the parts are made of different materials. Shine and feels of both the parts are also different.------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------This is my revised review, since the original was not publish due to incompliance of guidelines.Anyways, to sum up my original review, I received wrong item, thankfully amazon accepted return and I got the refund as well. Thumbs up to amazon for that !I however ended up buying this case from offline store. Now coming to important user experience,1. This is the hands down best case for Fold 6 in current market.2. Its very slim case, but has apt enough to protect the phone from drop impact.3. Material used is hard plastic and combo metal on inner back plate and camera bezels.4. S-pen bump isn't bothering me and rather acts as gripper assisting me to hold the phone even better.5. S pen is of perfect size and works like charm. Initially I was skeptical whether it will be small, but its just perfect for me.6. All the cutouts line up perfectly.CONS :-------1. The biggest downside off this case is the front left lip. As pointed by fellow reviewers and users, it comes with adhesive since there's very less surface area to latch onto. And this adhesive is WEAK !For me it just came of on 2nd day, though the front case doesn't come off because it has few more adhesive on other edges and fits perfectly. I was aware of this since I had already used 5 other cases and almost every case had this issue, so I was prepared with my solution.I had bought a 3mm double side adhesive for phone repair from amazon itself. I just had to line it up on the lip and had to trim just a bit using hobby knife and my issue was solved. Today while writing this review its 4th day and the adhesive i applied is holding up fine. I recommend buying 2mm tape instead, so trimming won't be needed and you can just cut and paste the tape.2. Normal tempered glass fits fine on with this case. But the one with black borders or so called 5D glass, won't fit with this case.3. Its overpriced !VERDICT :-----------For the given price of 8.5K its not worth at all, all the lip hassle thing.If you are getting this case for less than 6K, only then its worth the purchase. Else just buy s pen for 3k-4k and a decent case for 2k and you are good to go.
